39 to test the radar device for accuracy. The notice shall be given prior to the time a citation
40 and complaint or ticket is issued against the person and, if requested to make a test, the
41 officer shall test the radar device for accuracy. In the event the radar device does not meet
42 the minimum accuracy requirements, the citation and complaint or ticket shall not be issued
43 against the person, and the radar device shall be removed from service and thereafter shall
44 not be used by the county, municipal, or campus law enforcement agency until it has been
45 serviced, calibrated, and recertified by a technician with the qualifications specified in
46 Code Section 40-14-4.
47 (c)(1) The law enforcement agency, or agent on behalf of the law enforcement agency,
48 operating an automated traffic enforcement safety device provided for under Code
49 Section 40-14-18 shall maintain a log for the automated traffic enforcement safety device
50 attesting to the performance of such device's self-test at least once every 30 days and the
51 results of such self-test pertaining to the accuracy of the automated traffic enforcement
52 safety device. Such log shall be admissible in any court proceeding for a violation issued
53 pursuant to Code Section 40-14-18.
54 (2) The law enforcement agency, or agent on behalf of the law enforcement agency,
55 operating an automated traffic enforcement safety device shall perform an independent
56 calibration test on the automated traffic enforcement safety device at least once every 12
57 months. The results of such calibration test shall be admissible in any court proceeding
58 for a violation issued pursuant to Code Section 40-14-18."
